  "title": "How Codex and Anydocs Work Together",
  "description": "Put Codex inside an MCP-driven docs workflow.",
  "tags": [
    "codex",
    "workflow"
  ],
  "status": "published",
  "updatedAt": "2026-04-02T00:00:00.000Z",
  "content": {
    "version": 1,
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "id": "block-1",
        "level": 1,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How Codex and Anydocs Work Together"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "block-2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In Anydocs, Codex works best when it:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "id": "block-3",
        "style": "bulleted",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "element-3-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "reads the project contract first with `project_open`"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-4-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "checks `project_open.authoring` for templates, resources, and metadata schemas"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-5-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "reads `anydocs://authoring/guidance` when the task needs the full workflow"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-6-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "inspects current page state before choosing create versus update"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-7-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "uses `page_create_from_template`, `page_create`, or `page_update` for explicit changes"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-8-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "treats `page_set_status` as a separate workflow action"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-9-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "uses navigation MCP tools instead of rewriting navigation by hand"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "block-10",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The main idea is not to have Codex edit `pages/*.json` directly, but to keep it on MCP tools."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
